history.content:
I think to use the lab computers specifically you need to be enrolled in a class which uses the space; they'll then assign you a class username (e.g. cs61c-xxx) and password.

----------------------------------------------

If you're not enrolled in any classes that give account forms, you can also create an account that's just tied to you as a CS / EECS major (I don't think you can get one of these accounts if you're not a CS / EECS major, but I have no way of verifying that).  Those accounts also don't expire at the end of the semester, so it's nice to not have to repeatedly remember new passwords / remember how to change your password.  You can go to https://acropolis.cs.berkeley.edu/~account/webacct/ and log in with your Berkeley email to get the account (it will be named cs199-xxx).

children.subject: I don’t think so. Log into inst.eecs.berkeley.edu to retrieve your login information.

There is actually a website you can go to to print via your own computer (not sure if you have to be connected to AirBears2) and you just login with your EECS or Berkeley credentials. I forget the site but a classmate of mine showed it to me last semester. Sorry for the vague information, but just wanted to let you know the option exists, so you should ask another student or instructor/staff for more info!
